cmeta:comment.rdf:value: This is the main model component for the CellML encoding of the Cortassa et al (2006) Biophys J model.

rdf:Description.dc:publisher: Division of Bioengineering, National University of Singapore

cmeta:modification.rdf:value: Adding #clamp_ATPi and #clamp_ATPi_cyto variables to the model to allow the ATP concentration variables to be clamped in order to reproduce figure 6(a) from the original Cortassa et al (2006) Biophys J article.

cmeta:comment.rdf:value: This variable is used to clamp the value of [ATP]i at a constant value. The rate equation for [ATP]i is multiplied by the value (1-clamp_ATPi) - i.e., set clamp_ATPi = 1.0 in order to clamp the concentration.

This variable is used to clamp the value of [ATP]ic at a constant value. The rate equation for [ATP]ic is multiplied by the value (1-clamp_ATPi_cyto) - i.e., set clamp_ATPi_cyto = 1.0 in order to clamp the concentration.
